cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with video-based vehicle detection and tracking, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The proposed approach involves using shape prior and traffic force to handle occlusions and complex interactions among vehicles. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves modeling group behavior, which is related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques and sequential detection also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with surveillance videos, which may involve security and privacy concerns, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category as well.
